Celesio AG (CLS1) , Europeâ€™s biggest drug
wholesaler, reported a second-quarter loss after writing down
the value of businesses in Portugal and Denmark.  The loss was 86.9 million euros ($123.5 million) compared
with a profit of 50.3 million euros a year earlier, the
Stuttgart-based company said in a statement today. Earnings
before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization fell 24
percent to 130.2 million euros. Analysts predicted profit on
that basis of 126.1 million euros, the average of 13 estimates
